slider.faster: Accelerate your app development journey with our cutting-edge <bold>vendor agnostic</bold> and <bold>fully open-source</bold> platform designed for rapid innovatio and unbeatable efficiency.
slider.tools: All-in-one backend development. <bold>Database, authentication, app server, realtime, cron jobs, message queues </bold> â€” it's all here. Agnost gives developers the technologies to build scalable & secure backend apps in minutes.
slider.database: <bold>Build complex data models</bold> with relations, rich set of fields and built-in validation rules. Effortlessly manage your <bold>PostgreSQL, MySQL</bold> or <bold>MongoDB</bold> data with a powerful and intuitive user interface.
slider.serverless: Write simple, single-purpose functions that are attached to events emitted from your backend application. Your function is triggered when an event being watched is fired and your code is executed in a <bold>fully dedicated environment</bold> with <bold>auto-scaling capabilities</bold>.
slider.queue: Offload heavy computations from a parent service to a child one for <bold>asynchronous processing</bold> using <bold>RabbitMQ</bold> so that the parent service can return a response to the client faster and eventually improve response time.
slider.cron: <bold>Schedule jobs</bold> to run periodically at fixed times, dates, or intervals. Automate maintenance, administration, and repetitive jobs and make it useful for sending periodic emails, generating documents, performing bulk updates in the database.
slider.realtime: Listen to realtime changes with <bold>pub/sub pattern</bold> and <bold>broadcast</bold> the changes to the subscribers through realtime channels. Publish and subscribe to data streams in real-time using a simple and flexible API.
slider.security: Apply <bold>security policies</bold> to your backend services and functions. Secure your data and services with authentication, authorization, and encryption. Protect your services from malicious attacks and unauthorized access through <bold>API keys, rate limits, authorized origins</bold> and <bold>IP whitelisting</bold>.
